{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have a story, a story that I would like to share with you."},{"time":4000,"text":"And it's an African story."},{"time":6000,"text":"It is a story of hope, resilience and glamour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12000,"text":"There was Hollywood."},{"time":14000,"text":"Then came Bollywood."},{"time":17000,"text":"Today we have Nollywood, the third-largest film industry in the world."},{"time":24000,"text":"In 2006 alone, almost 2,000 films were made in Nigeria."},{"time":31000,"text":"Now, try to imagine 40, 50 films wrapped, distributed, every week"},{"time":39000,"text":"in the streets of Lagos, Nigeria and West Africa."},{"time":44000,"text":"Some estimates put the value of this industry at 250 million dollars."},{"time":50000,"text":"It has created thousands, if not tens of thousands of jobs."},{"time":56000,"text":"And it's expanding."},{"time":59000,"text":"But keep in mind that this was a grassroots movement."},{"time":67000,"text":"This is something that happened without foreign investment,"},{"time":73000,"text":"without government aid, and actually, it happened against all odds,"},{"time":79000,"text":"in one of the most difficult moments in Nigerian economy."},{"time":85000,"text":"The industry is 15 years old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"And so maybe you're thinking now,"},{"time":93000,"text":"why, how, an Italian filmmaker based in Boston"},{"time":97000,"text":"is so interested in this story?"},{"time":100000,"text":"And so I think I have to tell you just a few words,"},{"time":103000,"text":"a few things about my personal life,"},{"time":106000,"text":"because I think there is a connection."},{"time":112000,"text":"My grandfather lived most of his life and is buried in Zambia."},{"time":117000,"text":"My father also lived most of his adult life in East Africa."},{"time":123000,"text":"And I was born in Zambia."},{"time":127000,"text":"Even though I left when I was only three years old,"},{"time":129000,"text":"I really felt that Africa was this big part of my life."},{"time":134000,"text":"And it really was a place where I learned to walk."},{"time":139000,"text":"I think I uttered the first words,"},{"time":143000,"text":"and my family bought their first home."},{"time":145000,"text":"So when we came back to Italy,"},{"time":149000,"text":"and one of the things that I remember the most"},{"time":152000,"text":"is my family having this hard time to share stories."},{"time":156000,"text":"It seemed that for our neighbors and friends,"},{"time":159000,"text":"Africa was either this exotic place, this imaginary land"},{"time":165000,"text":"that probably exists only in their imagination,"},{"time":168000,"text":"or the place of horror, famine."},{"time":173000,"text":"And so we were always caught in this stereotype."},{"time":177000,"text":"And I remember really this desire to talk about Africa"},{"time":180000,"text":"as a place where we lived and people live and go about their lives,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and have dreams like we all have."},{"time":187000,"text":"So when I read in a newspaper in the business page"},{"time":193000,"text":"the story of Nollywood,"},{"time":195000,"text":"I really felt this is an incredible opportunity to tell a story"},{"time":200000,"text":"that goes against all these preconceived notions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"Here I can tell a story of Africans making movies like I do,"},{"time":209000,"text":"and actually I felt this was an inspiration for me."},{"time":215000,"text":"I have the good fortune of being a filmmaker-in-residence"},{"time":219000,"text":"at the Center of Digital Imaging Arts at Boston University."},{"time":222000,"text":"And we really look how digital technology is changing,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and how young, independent filmmakers"},{"time":229000,"text":"can make movies at a fraction of the cost."},{"time":232000,"text":"So when I proposed the story,"},{"time":234000,"text":"I really had all the support to make this film."},{"time":238000,"text":"And not only had the support,"},{"time":239000,"text":"I found two wonderful partners in crime in this adventure."},{"time":244000,"text":"Aimee Corrigan, a very talented and young photographer,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and Robert Caputo, a friend and a mentor,"},{"time":250000,"text":"who is a veteran of National Geographic,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and told me, \"You know, Franco, in 25 years of covering Africa,"},{"time":258000,"text":"I don't know if I have come across a story"},{"time":261000,"text":"that is so full of hope and so fun.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"So we went to Lagos in October 2005."},{"time":272000,"text":"And we went to Lagos to meet Bond Emeruwa,"},{"time":275000,"text":"a wonderful, talented film director who is with us tonight."},{"time":280000,"text":"The plan was to give you a portrait of Nollywood,"},{"time":284000,"text":"of this incredible film industry,"},{"time":287000,"text":"following Bond in his quest to make an action movie"},{"time":291000,"text":"that deals with the issue of corruption,"},{"time":294000,"text":"called \"Checkpoint.\""},{"time":296000,"text":"Police corruption."},{"time":298000,"text":"And he had nine days to make it."},{"time":300000,"text":"We thought this was a good story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"In the meantime, we had to cover Nollywood,"},{"time":305000,"text":"and we talked to a lot of filmmakers."},{"time":307000,"text":"But I don't want to create too many expectations."},{"time":309000,"text":"I would like to show you six minutes."},{"time":313000,"text":"And these are six minutes they really prepared for the TED audience."},{"time":317000,"text":"There are several themes from the documentary,"},{"time":320000,"text":"but they are re-edited and made for you, OK?"},{"time":322000,"text":"So I guess it's a world premier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"(Video)"},{"time":328000,"text":"Man: Action."},{"time":336000,"text":"Milverton Nwokedi: You cut a nice movie with just 10,000 dollars in Nigeria here."},{"time":343000,"text":"And you shoot in seven days."},{"time":350000,"text":"Peace Piberesima: We're doing films for the masses."},{"time":352000,"text":"We're not doing films for the elite"},{"time":354000,"text":"and the people in their glass houses."},{"time":356000,"text":"They can afford to watch their \"Robocop\" and whatever."},{"time":361000,"text":"Mahmood Ali Balogun: I think filmmaking in Nigeria, for those who work in it,"},{"time":363000,"text":"is a kind of subsistence filmmaking -- what they do to make a living."},{"time":367000,"text":"It's not the fancy filmmaking where you say,"},{"time":370000,"text":"oh, you want to put all the razzmatazz of Hollywood,"},{"time":373000,"text":"and where you have big budgets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"Here is that you make these films,"},{"time":377000,"text":"it sells, you jump onto the location again to make another film,"},{"time":381000,"text":"because if you don't make the next film, you're not going to feed."},{"time":391000,"text":"Bond Emeruwa: So while we're entertaining, we should be able to educate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"I believe in the power of audiovisuals."},{"time":399000,"text":"I mean, 90 percent of the population will watch Nollywood."},{"time":402000,"text":"I think it's the most viable vehicle right now"},{"time":404000,"text":"to pass information across a dedicated cable."},{"time":407000,"text":"So if you're making a movie, no matter what your topic is,"},{"time":410000,"text":"put in a message in there."},{"time":412000,"text":"Woman: You still have to report the incident."},{"time":417000,"text":"He needs proper medical attention."},{"time":420000,"text":"PP: I keep trying to explain to people,"},{"time":422000,"text":"it's not about the quality at the moment -- the quality is coming."},{"time":425000,"text":"I mean, there are those films that people are making for quality,"},{"time":429000,"text":"but the first thing you have to remember about this society"},{"time":432000,"text":"is that Africa still has people that live on one dollar a day,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and these are the people that really watch these films."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"Sonny McDon W: Nollywood is a fantastic industry"},{"time":448000,"text":"that has just been born in this part of the world."},{"time":456000,"text":"Because nobody believed that Nollywood can come out of Africa."},{"time":463000,"text":"Lancelot Imasen: But our films,"},{"time":465000,"text":"they are stories that our people can relate to themselves."},{"time":468000,"text":"They are stories about our people, for our people."},{"time":471000,"text":"And consistently, they are glued to their screen"},{"time":475000,"text":"whenever they see the story."},{"time":480000,"text":"Narrator: Suspense, fun and intrigue."},{"time":483000,"text":"It's the blockbuster comedy."},{"time":485000,"text":"You'll crack your ribs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"Bernard Pinayon Agbaosi: We have been so deep into the foreign movies."},{"time":497000,"text":"It's all about the foreign movies."},{"time":499000,"text":"But we can do something too."},{"time":501000,"text":"We can do something, something that when the world sees it,"},{"time":504000,"text":"they say, wow, this is Nigeria."},{"time":510000,"text":"Man: Just arrest yourself, sergeant."},{"time":512000,"text":"Don't embarrass yourself."},{"time":517000,"text":"Come on. Don't run away. Come back. Come back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524000,"text":"SMW: You can now walk the street and see a role model."},{"time":526000,"text":"It’s not just what you see in picture."},{"time":528000,"text":"You see the person live."},{"time":530000,"text":"You see how he talks. You see how he lives."},{"time":533000,"text":"He influences you really good, you know."},{"time":535000,"text":"It’s not just what you see in the picture."},{"time":537000,"text":"It is not what you hear, you know, from the Western press."},{"time":542000,"text":"Man: See you. Bye."},{"time":546000,"text":"Action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"Saint Obi: I was so fascinated, you know, with those cowboy movies."},{"time":554000,"text":"But then when I discovered the situation in my country,"},{"time":558000,"text":"at that time there was so much corruption."},{"time":562000,"text":"For a young man to really make it out here,"},{"time":565000,"text":"you got to think of some negative things and all that,"},{"time":569000,"text":"or some kind of vices."},{"time":571000,"text":"And I didn't want that, you know."},{"time":574000,"text":"And I discovered that I could be successful in life as an actor,"},{"time":579000,"text":"without doing crime, without cheating nobody, without telling no lies."},{"time":583000,"text":"Just me and God-given talent."},{"time":596000,"text":"Man: Let's go."},{"time":597000,"text":"OK, it's time to kick some ass."},{"time":602000,"text":"Cover this. It's your own."},{"time":605000,"text":"Move it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"Roboger Animadu: In big countries, when they do the movies,"},{"time":611000,"text":"they have all these things in place."},{"time":613000,"text":"But here, we improvise these items, like the gunshots."},{"time":617000,"text":"Like they go, here, now, now, you see the gun there,"},{"time":619000,"text":"but you won't see any guns shot, we use knock-out."},{"time":623000,"text":"Kevin Books Ikeduba: What I'm scared of is just the explosion will come up in my face."},{"time":626000,"text":"Woman: That's why I use enough masking tape."},{"time":628000,"text":"The masking tape will hold it."},{"time":630000,"text":"Wat, wait. Just hold this for me."},{"time":635000,"text":"KBI: I'm just telling her to make sure she places it well"},{"time":637000,"text":"so that it won't affect my face -- the explosion, you know."},{"time":639000,"text":"But she's a professional. She knows what she’s doing."},{"time":642000,"text":"I'm trying to protect my face too."},{"time":644000,"text":"This ain't going to be my last movie."},{"time":651000,"text":"You know, this is Nollywood, where the magic lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"RA: So now you're about to see how we do our own movies here,"},{"time":658000,"text":"with or without any assistance from anybody."},{"time":662000,"text":"Man: Action."},{"time":667000,"text":"Cut."},{"time":669000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"Franco Sacchi: So many things to say, so little time."},{"time":677000,"text":"So many themes in this story."},{"time":679000,"text":"I just can't tell you -- there’s one thing I want to tell you."},{"time":682000,"text":"I spent, you know, several weeks with all these actors, producers,"},{"time":687000,"text":"and the problems they have to go through are unimaginable"},{"time":690000,"text":"for, you know, a Westerner, a filmmaker who works in America or in Europe."},{"time":694000,"text":"But always with a smile, always with an enthusiasm,"},{"time":698000,"text":"that is incredible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700000,"text":"Werner Herzog, the German filmmaker said,"},{"time":702000,"text":"\"I need to make movies like you need oxygen.\""},{"time":707000,"text":"And I think they’re breathing."},{"time":709000,"text":"The Nigerian filmmakers really, really, are doing what they like."},{"time":713000,"text":"And so it's a very, very important thing for them,"},{"time":717000,"text":"and for their audiences."},{"time":718000,"text":"A woman told me, \"When I see a Nollywood film,"},{"time":721000,"text":"I can relax, I really -- I can breathe better.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"There is also another very important thing"},{"time":727000,"text":"that I hope will resonate with this audience."},{"time":729000,"text":"It’s technology. I’m very interested in it"},{"time":732000,"text":"and I really think that the digital non-linear editing has slashed, you know,"},{"time":739000,"text":"the cost now is a fraction of what it used to be."},{"time":741000,"text":"Incredible cameras cost under 5,000 dollars."},{"time":745000,"text":"And this has unleashed tremendous energy."},{"time":748000,"text":"And guess what?"},{"time":750000,"text":"We didn’t have to tell to the Nigerian filmmakers."},{"time":752000,"text":"They understood it, they embraced the technology"},{"time":755000,"text":"and they run with it, and they’re successful."},{"time":757000,"text":"I hope that the Nollywood phenomenon will go both ways."},{"time":762000,"text":"I hope it will inspire other African nations to embrace the technology,"},{"time":767000,"text":"look at the Nigerian model, make their films, create jobs,"},{"time":770000,"text":"create a narrative for the population, something to identify,"},{"time":774000,"text":"something positive, something that really is psychological relief"},{"time":777000,"text":"and it's part of the culture."},{"time":779000,"text":"But I really think this is a phenomenon that can inspire us."},{"time":784000,"text":"I really think it goes both ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786000,"text":"Filmmakers, friends of mine, they look at Nollywood and they say,"},{"time":790000,"text":"\"Wow, they are doing what we really want to do,"},{"time":792000,"text":"and make a buck and live with this job.\""},{"time":795000,"text":"So I really think it’s a lesson"},{"time":796000,"text":"that we're actually learning from them."},{"time":798000,"text":"And there's one thing, one small challenge that I have for you,"},{"time":801000,"text":"and should make us reflect on the importance of storytelling."},{"time":805000,"text":"And I think this is really the theme of this session."},{"time":808000,"text":"Try to imagine a world where the only goal is food and a shelter, but no stories."},{"time":820000,"text":"No stories around the campfire."},{"time":822000,"text":"No legends, no fairytales."},{"time":824000,"text":"Nothing."},{"time":826000,"text":"No novels."},{"time":831000,"text":"Difficult, eh? It's meaningless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833000,"text":"So this is what I really think."},{"time":836000,"text":"I think that the key to a healthy society"},{"time":840000,"text":"is a thriving community of storytellers,"},{"time":842000,"text":"and I think that the Nigerian filmmakers really have proved this."},{"time":847000,"text":"I would like you to hear their voices."},{"time":852000,"text":"Just a few moments."},{"time":855000,"text":"It’s not an added sequence, just some voices from Nollywood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860000,"text":"(Video) Toyin Alousa: Nollywood is the best thing that can happen to them."},{"time":862000,"text":"If you have an industry that puts a smile on people's face,"},{"time":866000,"text":"that’s Nollywood."},{"time":868000,"text":"SO: I believe very soon, we’re not only going to have better movies,"},{"time":871000,"text":"we'll have that original Nigerian movie."},{"time":874000,"text":"BE: It’s still the same basic themes."},{"time":876000,"text":"Love, action."},{"time":880000,"text":"But we're telling it our own way, our own Nigerian way, African way."},{"time":886000,"text":"We have diverse cultures, diverse cultures, there are so many,"},{"time":891000,"text":"that in the natal lifetimes,"},{"time":894000,"text":"I don't see us exhausting the stories we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"FS: My job ends here, and the Nollywood filmmakers really have now to work."},{"time":905000,"text":"And I really hope that there will be many, many collaborations,"},{"time":910000,"text":"where we teach each other things."},{"time":912000,"text":"And I really hope that this will happen."},{"time":915000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":916000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Stop. I've got two questions."},{"time":924000,"text":"Franco, you described this as the world's third largest film industry."},{"time":929000,"text":"What does that translate to in terms of numbers of films, really?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"FS: Oh, yes. I think I mentioned briefly -- it's close to 2,000 films."},{"time":936000,"text":"There is scientific data on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":938000,"text":"CA: 2,000 films a year?"},{"time":940000,"text":"FS: 2,000 films a year. 2005 or 6,"},{"time":943000,"text":"the censor board has censored 1,600 films alone."},{"time":949000,"text":"And we know that there are more."},{"time":951000,"text":"So it’s safe to say that there are 2,000 films."},{"time":953000,"text":"So imagine 45 films per week."},{"time":955000,"text":"There are challenges. There are challenges."},{"time":957000,"text":"There is a glut of film,"},{"time":959000,"text":"the quality has to be raised, they need to go to the next level,"},{"time":962000,"text":"but I’m optimistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"CA: And these aren’t films that are primarily seen in cinemas?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":967000,"text":"FS: Oh yes, of course. This is very important."},{"time":970000,"text":"Maybe, you know, for you to try to imagine this,"},{"time":972000,"text":"these are films that are distributed directly in markets."},{"time":978000,"text":"They are bought in video shops."},{"time":980000,"text":"They can be rented for pennies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982000,"text":"CA: On what format?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":983000,"text":"FS: Oh, the format -- thank you for the question. Yes, it's VCDs."},{"time":986000,"text":"It's a CD, it's a little bit more compressed image."},{"time":989000,"text":"They started with VHS."},{"time":991000,"text":"They actually didn't wait for, you know, the latest technology."},{"time":994000,"text":"They started in '92, '94."},{"time":996000,"text":"So there are 57 million VCRs in Nigeria"},{"time":1002000,"text":"that play, you know, VHS and these VCDs."},{"time":1006000,"text":"It's a CD basically. It's a compact disc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008000,"text":"CA: So on the streets, are film casts ... ?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010000,"text":"FS: You can be in a Lagos traffic jam"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and you can buy a movie or some bananas or some water. Yes."},{"time":1018000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1020000,"text":"And I have to say, this really proves that storytelling,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"it's a commodity, it's a staple."},{"time":1026000,"text":"There is no life without stories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"CA: Franco, thank you so much."}]}]}